00:45.337 --> 00:46.457
And that <i>wraps it up</i>

00:46.547 --> 00:48.467
<i>for today's pop culture
and celebrity news.</i>

00:48.549 --> 00:51.509
<i>Now, let's throw it over
to our very own Nikki Boyer</i>

00:51.593 --> 00:53.643
<i>for this week's
"where are they now?" Segment.</i>

00:57.641 --> 00:59.691
In tonight's
"where are they now?" Segment,

00:59.768 --> 01:02.728
we take a look at
child star Gavin stone.

01:02.813 --> 01:05.072
Twenty years ago, stone shot
to small-screen stardom

01:05.147 --> 01:08.068
<i>as cliffy in the smash
sitcom family life.</i>

01:08.151 --> 01:10.241
And had seemingly
every kid in America saying...

01:10.320 --> 01:11.860
Don't look at me.

01:11.947 --> 01:14.277
<i>His legendary manager,
star maker, Jack Roth,</i>

01:14.366 --> 01:17.236
<i>parlayed that into
merchandise, a cliffy DVD,</i>

01:17.327 --> 01:20.077
<i>and after family life's
cancellation,</i> a <i>couple of movies.</i>

01:20.163 --> 01:22.373
And then, tragedy struck.

01:22.457 --> 01:24.417
The unexpected
death of Gavin's mother

01:24.501 --> 01:27.051
ultimately led to
a messy emancipation

01:27.129 --> 01:29.669
from his now
estranged father, Waylon.

01:29.756 --> 01:31.626
<i>Exercising his newfound freedom,</i>

01:31.717 --> 01:34.427
<i>Gavin became a fixture
on the party scene.</i>

01:34.511 --> 01:38.391
But, five years ago, his fast
living finally caught up with him.

01:38.473 --> 01:40.353
<i>After consecutive
stints in rehab,</i>

01:40.434 --> 01:42.644
<i>stone has been mostly
out of the public eye.</i>

01:42.728 --> 01:44.898
<i>Otherwise,
his career has stalled.</i>

01:44.980 --> 01:48.610
Even his former director and creator
of <i>family life,</i> Mike Meara,

01:48.692 --> 01:52.572
reportedly didn't even audition
stone for Meara's new TV series.

01:52.696 --> 01:56.526
Ouch. It looks like his career
will remain quiet for a while,

01:56.617 --> 01:58.827
much to the delight
of movie critics.

01:58.910 --> 02:01.370
So there you have it,
"where is he now?"

02:03.415 --> 02:06.335
<i>Gavin, I'm your manager,
not</i> a <i>miracle worker.</i>

02:06.418 --> 02:07.838
<i>The party went
too far this time.</i>

02:07.919 --> 02:10.378
You trashed
the entire rooftop of a hotel.

02:10.881 --> 02:12.051
Take a look.

02:14.092 --> 02:15.342
Memory still failing you?

02:15.427 --> 02:17.717
Is that a catapult?

02:18.055 --> 02:19.055
Yes.

02:19.389 --> 02:22.389
Gavin, listen,
the damage is your fault.

02:22.809 --> 02:25.019
This judge won't budge
on community service.

02:25.103 --> 02:26.693
Community service?

02:26.772 --> 02:28.572
Maintenance at a local church.

02:28.815 --> 02:30.065
Church?

02:30.317 --> 02:34.197
Like, god and choirs
and all that?

02:34.279 --> 02:35.739
Or sewage cleanup.

02:36.073 --> 02:39.283
Is there a difference?
Gavin. Take the deal.

02:39.368 --> 02:42.368
Spend 200 hours of your life doing
something positive for a change.

02:42.454 --> 02:44.794
In Masonville, Illinois?

02:44.873 --> 02:46.123
I got out of here for a reason.

02:46.208 --> 02:48.498
Please, guys, remind me
never to visit again.

02:48.585 --> 02:50.085
You got no choice, okay?

02:50.170 --> 02:51.400
So, I want you
to deal with this,

02:51.421 --> 02:52.661
and I want you to make it work.

02:53.924 --> 02:56.094
Reconnect with your old man.

02:56.510 --> 02:58.350
You're gonna need
a place to stay.

02:58.428 --> 02:59.928
I prefer jail.

03:03.433 --> 03:05.813
Okay, fine.
The church thing.

03:06.395 --> 03:08.435
Be on time, be respectful.

03:08.605 --> 03:10.225
You listening?
Yes.

03:10.315 --> 03:11.855
Don't screw this up.

03:11.942 --> 03:13.362
How could I?

03:13.443 --> 03:14.993
I'll fit right in.

03:26.123 --> 03:28.923
<i>This is Mike Meara.
Who are you?</i>

03:29.543 --> 03:33.553
Hey, hey, Mikey. Gavin stone.

03:33.630 --> 03:36.010
Just wanted to see
if you needed, uh...

03:36.341 --> 03:37.381
Um...

03:37.467 --> 03:39.387
<i>To leave
your message, press two.</i>

03:39.469 --> 03:41.809
<i>To re-record, press three.</i>

03:45.392 --> 03:48.152
Mike, my man.

03:48.228 --> 03:52.148
Hey, still owe you that drink
from a few years back.

04:00.240 --> 04:05.580
Good day, Mr. Meara. I just
wanted to reintroduce myself.

04:05.662 --> 04:06.662
My name is Gavin stone.

04:36.735 --> 04:37.735
It'll be fine.

04:38.403 --> 04:40.453
He's your dad.
Just tell him what happened.

04:40.530 --> 04:41.820
Tell him you're sorry.

04:42.574 --> 04:43.624
He'll be fine.

04:45.660 --> 04:48.120
Well, thanks for the ride.

04:48.538 --> 04:49.578
Good luck.

05:17.317 --> 05:18.317
Dad.

05:24.908 --> 05:25.908
You in trouble?

05:26.409 --> 05:27.699
Uh...

05:28.495 --> 05:29.695
A little.

05:31.373 --> 05:32.713
What kind?

05:34.167 --> 05:36.087
The kind where you
can't leave the state

05:36.169 --> 05:38.379
until you've completed
your community service hours.

05:38.463 --> 05:39.923
What did you do this time?

05:40.507 --> 05:41.757
Long story.

05:43.093 --> 05:44.093
You clean?

05:45.846 --> 05:47.596
Yes.
Are you clean?

05:48.849 --> 05:50.979
Dad, yes.

05:53.186 --> 05:54.186
Been a while.

05:56.314 --> 05:58.784
Yeah. Yeah, it has.

05:59.150 --> 06:02.610
Place looks nice.

06:02.821 --> 06:05.121
No, it doesn't. Not yet.

06:06.116 --> 06:09.196
Well, you know,
you finished the outside...

06:09.286 --> 06:10.286
Eight years ago.

06:15.041 --> 06:16.131
Okay.

06:16.209 --> 06:19.669
Um, look, I'm just
gonna come out with it.

06:19.754 --> 06:21.634
I need a place to stay.

06:23.216 --> 06:25.256
Low on cash,
and I don't have a gig, so...

06:25.552 --> 06:27.182
Say what you need to say.

06:31.433 --> 06:34.603
It's been a one-man band
around here for a long time.

06:34.686 --> 06:36.226
Yeah, I know.

06:38.481 --> 06:40.151
But if you have a spare room,

06:41.151 --> 06:43.701
I promise
I'll stay out of your way.

06:51.953 --> 06:54.003
I don't have maid service.

06:54.080 --> 06:56.000
This isn't the motel 6.

06:56.166 --> 06:58.336
If you're out late, the
light's not left on for you.

07:01.171 --> 07:02.671
How long are you
gonna be around?

07:02.756 --> 07:04.666
Uh, two hundred hours.

07:04.966 --> 07:08.846
And unless you can drive me, I'm
gonna need to borrow the truck.

07:09.179 --> 07:12.269
The 16th birthday truck
that you turned down

07:12.349 --> 07:14.269
'cause you wanted to
buy a Vette, that truck?

07:14.351 --> 07:15.561
Yes, dad, that is the one.

07:16.686 --> 07:18.146
Have at it.
Thank you.

07:18.229 --> 07:23.109
Oh, I gotta be at Masonville Bible church.
You've ever been there?

07:23.193 --> 07:26.283
I go to about as many
church services as you do.

07:27.197 --> 07:29.697
Well, this should be fun.

07:46.257 --> 07:47.757
Come on.

08:18.581 --> 08:21.421
Thank you, father, for this
opportunity we have...

08:31.720 --> 08:34.640
Toto, we are not in
Los Angeles anymore.

08:42.147 --> 08:43.227
Hello?

08:45.650 --> 08:49.030
Hey, do you know
where the pastor's office is?

08:49.112 --> 08:50.282
I do.

08:51.156 --> 08:53.276
You're Gavin stone.
All right.

08:54.451 --> 08:56.871
Let's do it fast, man.
You got your phone?

08:57.120 --> 08:59.460
I'm sorry? I'm happy to do a selfie.
You're a fan, right?

08:59.998 --> 09:02.328
Of what?
Me, the show...

09:02.417 --> 09:04.497
I mean,
you recognized me, right?

09:04.586 --> 09:06.876
Should I?
How did you know my name?

09:07.714 --> 09:10.634
It was printed at
the top of your rap sheet.

09:10.717 --> 09:13.967
I'm Allan Richardson.
Pastor Allan Richardson.

09:14.637 --> 09:15.637
Ah.

09:16.264 --> 09:18.934
So, why are you fixing the...
Because it's broken.

09:19.517 --> 09:22.647
"Drink from your own
cistern." Proverb, sort of.

09:23.480 --> 09:26.360
And at 30 bucks an hour, always
better to fix it yourself.

09:26.816 --> 09:28.566
I didn't know pastors did that.

09:28.818 --> 09:32.068
Well, I guess you
haven't met many pastors.

09:32.405 --> 09:35.775
The catapult was a nice touch.
Quite a party, huh?

09:35.867 --> 09:37.987
They gave you the pictures.

09:38.078 --> 09:41.288
I've been a pastor for decades.
Nothing shocks me anymore.

09:41.372 --> 09:44.082
I really wasn't a part of...
Yeah, they told me the story.

09:44.167 --> 09:46.747
You're not the best decision
maker, but you're no criminal.

09:46.836 --> 09:49.086
So, we don't need to share
with anybody why you're here.

09:49.172 --> 09:51.862
It's a big church, you'll fly under the
radar, everybody'll treat you great.

09:51.883 --> 09:53.013
Okay. Got it.

09:53.093 --> 09:56.013
Gavin, we really do believe
in second chances here.

09:56.096 --> 09:58.136
But they're not
to be taken lightly.

09:58.223 --> 10:00.603
200 hours means 200 hours.

10:00.683 --> 10:03.603
And don't just think because
I'm the "caring pastor"

10:03.686 --> 10:05.396
that you're gonna
put one over on me.

10:05.480 --> 10:06.610
Got it?

10:07.190 --> 10:08.980
Got it.
Good.

10:09.067 --> 10:11.107
So, father...

10:11.569 --> 10:13.449
"Pastor" is fine.
Or just Allan.

10:13.530 --> 10:15.030
Okay. Yeah, Allan...

10:15.365 --> 10:16.655
Uh...

10:16.741 --> 10:19.081
What is it exactly
that I'll be doing?

10:42.058 --> 10:43.058
Ha!

10:43.685 --> 10:44.685
Hiya!

10:44.727 --> 10:45.897
Whoa.

10:46.104 --> 10:47.654
Uh...
What are you doing?

10:47.730 --> 10:48.900
Nothing.

10:48.982 --> 10:51.482
Sorry, I'm not, uh...

10:52.152 --> 10:54.072
You know, just cleaning.

10:54.404 --> 10:55.614
Where is Helen?

10:55.697 --> 10:58.987
I'm just filling in for Helen.

10:59.075 --> 11:00.945
Okay, well,
you need to put a sign

11:01.035 --> 11:02.825
because this is
the women's bathroom.

11:02.912 --> 11:05.212
Yup. Should have
done that, yeah.

11:05.623 --> 11:07.083
Do I know you from somewhere?

11:08.251 --> 11:09.251
You recognize me?

11:09.586 --> 11:11.426
I don't think I've seen you
around here before.

11:11.546 --> 11:13.126
You can figure it out later.

11:13.214 --> 11:16.344
Maybe over coffee
or deep-dish pizza.

11:16.426 --> 11:18.296
You guys are into that, right?
Really?

11:18.386 --> 11:22.016
Yeah, thin crust is fine, too.

11:22.765 --> 11:25.435
Uh... well,
I got a ton of work to do,

11:25.560 --> 11:28.270
and I've known you for 30 seconds, so...

11:29.647 --> 11:30.817
Ls that...

11:31.816 --> 11:33.476
Are these movie scenes?

11:33.568 --> 11:36.948
Uh, no. It is our annual
stage production.

11:37.030 --> 11:39.700
That's totally my thing.
I could help you with that.

11:39.782 --> 11:43.452
Right now, you can help me
by cleaning another bathroom.

11:43.536 --> 11:45.706
'Cause this is the women's.

11:45.788 --> 11:46.998
Yeah. Hmm.

11:47.081 --> 11:48.921
Yep. All right.

11:49.000 --> 11:52.380
I'll just get a sign.

12:09.270 --> 12:10.520
As well.

12:10.605 --> 12:12.815
I can sing, I can dance...

12:14.067 --> 12:15.987
Okay, next up is Charles.

12:23.952 --> 12:29.672
Woe to you, scribes and pharisees.
Woe to you.

12:29.749 --> 12:32.749
Hi. My name is Doug.
I've never acted before.

12:32.835 --> 12:35.375
But I'm willing to serve the lord
in whatever way you see fit.

12:35.463 --> 12:38.513
My name is
Charlotte Elizabeth Stewart.

12:38.591 --> 12:40.721
I'm the stage manager.

12:40.802 --> 12:44.142
And I'm going to be
performing amazing grace.

12:45.223 --> 12:50.443
My name is Anthony Mathias
Roundstone, and I live for Jesus.

12:50.770 --> 12:53.730
The stage is a close second.

12:53.815 --> 13:00.355
I'll be performing a monologue from
Henrik Ibsen's <i>a</i> doll's house.

13:01.948 --> 13:03.118
Finished already?

13:04.534 --> 13:05.584
You know what they say.

13:05.660 --> 13:09.000
Time flies when you're serving your
state-mandated community service hours.

13:09.080 --> 13:10.620
Eight down, 192 to go.

13:10.707 --> 13:14.957
You know, as naturally
gifted as I am with a mop,

13:15.044 --> 13:17.464
I'm 10 times better on stage.

13:17.714 --> 13:21.474
You think I could spend a few
of my hours working on this?

13:21.551 --> 13:23.271
Maybe help you guys out?
Oh, that'd be nice.

13:23.303 --> 13:25.893
But, uh, this is one
of our ministries.

13:25.972 --> 13:28.602
We ask that all cast members
be believing Christians.

13:34.480 --> 13:35.520
Well, lam one.

13:36.649 --> 13:38.569
You are what?
Christian.

13:39.110 --> 13:40.610
You're a Christian?
Yes.

13:40.695 --> 13:42.275
You are?
Yes.

13:42.363 --> 13:44.123
Really?
You didn't know that?

13:44.699 --> 13:46.010
I must have missed it
in your file

13:46.034 --> 13:47.664
between the drunk
and disorderly charges.

13:48.036 --> 13:49.076
Ah.

13:49.370 --> 13:50.500
Touché, touché.

13:50.580 --> 13:53.920
No, I'm Christian.
Capital c.

13:54.000 --> 14:00.420
I've had the passion of the
Christ for a couple of years now.

14:02.008 --> 14:06.388
As in, you believe that Jesus
Christ is the son of god?

14:06.471 --> 14:07.511
God.

14:07.597 --> 14:09.927
And that he's our savior?
Savior, yeah.

14:10.016 --> 14:11.226
Really?
Mmm-hmm.

14:12.310 --> 14:14.190
I've had my share of
hiccups, as you know.

14:14.687 --> 14:18.607
A couple of nights ago,
was a mistake, obviously,

14:19.525 --> 14:22.105
but it's no mistake
that I chose to come here.

14:24.655 --> 14:25.655
Why didn't you tell me?

14:27.533 --> 14:30.703
I don't know. Just didn't
think you'd believe me.

14:30.787 --> 14:33.367
Not sure if you do now.
No, no. I...

14:34.290 --> 14:35.790
I didn't expect it.

14:36.125 --> 14:38.035
Just so you know,
newcomers are expected

14:38.127 --> 14:40.127
to share their testimony
when they audition.

14:40.421 --> 14:41.881
Oh.
Okay?

14:41.964 --> 14:43.634
Done that plenty of times.

14:43.716 --> 14:46.386
No, I don't mean
the kind you do in court.

14:47.345 --> 14:50.845
Yeah. Yeah. I know.

14:50.973 --> 14:52.733
Okay. Okay?

14:52.809 --> 14:53.979
Of course.
All right.

14:55.228 --> 14:56.478
All right.

15:00.483 --> 15:01.783
All right.

15:02.819 --> 15:06.779
Christian testimony.
Christian testimony.

15:06.864 --> 15:08.994
Bono? But he's so cool.

15:09.242 --> 15:14.622
Hello. My name is John mark. And I'm
auditioning for the role of Peter...

15:14.705 --> 15:15.745
Uh, hi.
Hi.

15:15.832 --> 15:17.582
I'm Gavin, I'm here for Jesus.

15:17.667 --> 15:19.417
Oh, that's sweet.
Me, too.

15:20.420 --> 15:22.380
Oh, yeah, yeah.
That, too.

15:22.505 --> 15:25.505
Uh, no, I'm here for the role of Jesus.
Oh. Oh! Uh...

15:25.591 --> 15:28.471
John mark is going up now, and
you can go on up after him.

15:28.553 --> 15:30.053
Okay. Oh...

15:31.097 --> 15:32.097
Got it.

15:32.181 --> 15:35.441
Go quickly and tell his
disciples that he has risen.

15:35.643 --> 15:36.643
Thank you.

15:36.686 --> 15:38.396
Thank you.

15:38.479 --> 15:40.689
Okay, is that it?
No, no.

15:41.858 --> 15:43.778
Great job, buddy.
Oh, gosh.

15:43.860 --> 15:45.860
Should I stand here?
Yeah, that's fine.

15:45.945 --> 15:47.235
Since this is your first time,

15:47.321 --> 15:49.241
we ask that you
share a little bit...

15:49.323 --> 15:51.373
Ah, my testimony.
Yes, yes.

15:51.451 --> 15:52.851
That's Gavin stone. Gavin:
Pastor Allan mentioned that.

15:52.869 --> 15:55.222
Then go right ahead and then you can
go into your reading after that.

15:55.246 --> 15:58.536
All right, all right.
Let's do this.

15:58.708 --> 16:00.788
Hi, everybody. Um...

16:00.877 --> 16:04.207
As you probably already know,
my name is Gavin stone.

16:04.547 --> 16:07.587
Oh... that's where I recognized him from.
What is he doing here?

16:07.675 --> 16:11.465
But what you probably didn't
know is that I'm a Christian.

16:11.554 --> 16:13.474
I wasn't until a few years ago

16:13.556 --> 16:17.556
when I hit rock-bottom and
just felt something missing.

16:18.686 --> 16:21.306
Guess you could call
it a god-shaped hole.

16:21.981 --> 16:23.731
So, I came to a place

16:23.816 --> 16:29.106
where I decided to climb
that stairway to heaven

16:29.822 --> 16:32.532
and let Jesus take the wheel.

16:32.617 --> 16:38.247
And ultimately, uh,
hey, let go and let god.

16:38.539 --> 16:39.749
Mmm. Mmm-hmm.

16:40.041 --> 16:41.291
I'm still a bit new to it, too.

16:41.375 --> 16:44.995
Forgive me if I don't always
get the details perfect.

16:45.087 --> 16:46.417
- Uh...
- Thank you.

16:46.714 --> 16:49.094
If I may ask, what are you
doing here in Masonville?

16:49.759 --> 16:51.299
Well, this is my hometown.

16:52.178 --> 16:54.928
I had a bit of
a rough patch recently.

16:55.014 --> 16:57.934
And ultimately, I had no choice
but to come home to my father.

16:59.977 --> 17:02.357
Anyway, I thought,
"hey, while I was here,

17:02.438 --> 17:04.728
"I could help out
on stage, too."

17:04.815 --> 17:08.025
So, I'm auditioning for
the role of Jesus Christ.

17:08.402 --> 17:09.742
Superstar.

17:10.988 --> 17:13.818
Theater joke. Anyway, uh, this
is a speech from Hamlet.

17:14.325 --> 17:17.535
He's anguished and alone
after his father's death.

17:23.626 --> 17:26.955
O, that this too too
solid flesh would melt,

17:28.130 --> 17:31.880
thaw, and resolve
itself into a dew!

17:32.885 --> 17:35.715
Or that the everlasting
had not fix'd

17:35.805 --> 17:38.175
his canon
'gainst self-slaughter!

17:39.350 --> 17:46.270
How weary, stale,
flat, and unprofitable,

17:46.357 --> 17:49.987
seems to me all
the uses of this world!

17:51.571 --> 17:57.201
Fie on't! Oh fie, fie!
'Tis an unweeded garden,

17:57.285 --> 18:02.075
that grows to seed, things
rank and gross in nature

18:02.164 --> 18:05.294
possess it merely.
That it should come to this!

18:06.168 --> 18:11.918
But two months dead!
Nay, not so much, not two.

18:12.008 --> 18:13.338
Okay, thank you.

18:13.593 --> 18:15.513
I had... I had more.

18:15.595 --> 18:17.715
That's okay.
We got it. Very good.

18:17.972 --> 18:20.642
Good'? That was incredible.
Okay.

18:20.975 --> 18:22.015
Good.

18:22.935 --> 18:24.555
- Awesome!
- Nice.

18:25.104 --> 18:27.364
- Okay. Thank you.
- Whoo!

18:30.109 --> 18:31.279
Whoo-hoo!

18:38.117 --> 18:40.287
So, why didn't he tell us?

18:40.369 --> 18:42.329
I told him what I tell
everybody who does this.

18:42.413 --> 18:45.043
Nobody needs to know the
details of why you're here.

18:46.208 --> 18:48.338
So, you saw it? I was
watching from the back.

18:48.419 --> 18:49.709
He's very good.

18:50.046 --> 18:53.126
Yes, dad, he's good.
Obviously.

18:53.215 --> 18:55.455
But do we really want the most
important part of the play

18:55.509 --> 18:56.719
to be done by a newcomer?

18:56.802 --> 18:58.972
Especially somebody who
brings all this attention.

18:59.055 --> 19:01.305
