51:49.523 --> 51:50.983
It is a mess.

51:51.525 --> 51:53.235
But it's not empty.

52:02.453 --> 52:05.833
You're listening to WAAY,
the best in Christian radio.

52:05.914 --> 52:08.044
This is the morning sun
with Wayne McCusker.

52:08.125 --> 52:09.853
So, hey, we have a special
guest with us this morning.

52:09.877 --> 52:11.707
But I don't need
to tell you who it is,

52:11.795 --> 52:15.165
you should be able to figure
it out when he says this...

52:16.508 --> 52:18.588
Don't look at me.
There it is.

52:18.677 --> 52:21.031
And of course, you can't look at
him 'cause he's on the radio.

52:21.055 --> 52:22.335
But if you're over 30 years old,

52:22.389 --> 52:25.559
you know that sentence comes from
former child star, Gavin stone,

52:25.643 --> 52:26.833
who's here with us this morning.

52:26.852 --> 52:29.362
Hey, Gavin. Or shall I call you cliffy?

52:29.605 --> 52:31.105
Uh, no, Gavin's fine.

52:31.190 --> 52:33.980
So, cliffy, you used to play in a
lot of roles on TV and movies,

52:34.068 --> 52:37.318
but you're here today to talk
to us about a special new role.

52:37.404 --> 52:40.244
One that might just be the most
special role of your life.

52:40.324 --> 52:41.494
Am I right?
Um...

52:41.575 --> 52:42.785
Tell us about it.
Okay.

52:42.868 --> 52:44.868
Well, it's called
crown of thorns.

52:44.953 --> 52:47.083
We're doing it at
the Masonville Bible church.

52:47.164 --> 52:49.674
It is directed by the fabulous Ms.
Kelly Richardson.

52:49.750 --> 52:51.394
And, Kelly, you snagged
cliffy for the part of...

52:51.418 --> 52:52.748
Jesus, yes.

52:53.253 --> 52:54.253
He's doing a great job.

52:54.546 --> 52:56.006
So, cliffy, let's talk.

52:56.507 --> 52:57.967
Aren't we...

52:58.050 --> 53:00.140
I'd love to hear about
your heart transformation.

53:00.219 --> 53:03.429
How has the blood of Christ
impacted your own walk?

53:04.139 --> 53:05.950
I'm sorry, what? Share with
us the spiritual journey

53:05.974 --> 53:06.984
that got you here.

53:07.059 --> 53:08.389
From sinner to savior.

53:08.477 --> 53:10.187
My spiritual journey?

53:10.479 --> 53:12.859
Well, I'd love to
tell you all about it,

53:12.940 --> 53:18.530
but, honestly, this production
isn't about Gavin stone.

53:18.612 --> 53:23.282
I'm really hoping and praying

53:23.701 --> 53:27.331
that when people come to see
this show, they don't see me.

53:28.288 --> 53:31.458
That I've gotten so lost in this
character, that they just see him

53:32.251 --> 53:34.591
and the story and
the rest of the cast.

53:34.670 --> 53:37.130
I don't want to be
a distraction to that.

53:37.589 --> 53:38.629
Wow.

53:41.593 --> 53:42.643
Teacher!

53:44.096 --> 53:47.466
This woman was
caught in adultery.

53:48.016 --> 53:51.266
You know the law, she must
be stoned for this sin.

53:51.353 --> 53:53.483
I'm writing?
Sorry, sorry.

53:53.731 --> 53:55.901
Uh, dumb question.
What is he writing?

53:55.983 --> 53:57.283
It doesn't say in the script.

53:57.359 --> 53:58.989
Because it's not in the Bible.

53:59.069 --> 54:00.949
Really? Why not?

54:01.029 --> 54:04.199
I guess 'cause it's not
the focus of the scene.

54:04.283 --> 54:05.993
But just improvise.

54:06.076 --> 54:07.076
Okay.
Okay?

54:07.161 --> 54:08.541
Keep going.

54:09.329 --> 54:11.919
This woman has sinned
against heaven.

54:11.999 --> 54:14.039
What shall be done with her?

54:14.668 --> 54:18.628
Let he who is without sin,
cast the first stone.

54:23.802 --> 54:28.062
My sister, where are
your accusers now?

54:28.140 --> 54:31.230
Does even one remain
to condemn you?

54:31.310 --> 54:32.690
None, lord.

54:32.770 --> 54:34.270
Neither do I.

54:35.439 --> 54:37.519
Go and sin no more.

54:38.650 --> 54:40.530
Yeah. Uh...

54:40.986 --> 54:41.986
This doesn't work.

54:42.112 --> 54:43.912
What's up? I thought it looked good.
Okay.

54:44.156 --> 54:45.866
You're doing great. Uh...

54:46.450 --> 54:49.330
First of all, why does
he even defend her?

54:49.411 --> 54:51.041
Does he know her?

54:51.580 --> 54:53.620
I've got this, Kelly.
Let me... yeah.

54:54.082 --> 54:56.172
It's called the
doctrine of atonement.

54:56.251 --> 54:59.211
What it means, is the
totality of human inequity

54:59.463 --> 55:03.933
can only be removed by the one who
establishes those moral parameters.

55:04.009 --> 55:06.299
However... uh, John
mark, not right now.

55:06.386 --> 55:08.056
But... we can talk
about it later.

55:08.388 --> 55:11.888
The whole thing
just feels so, um...

55:15.813 --> 55:17.403
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
Where were we?

55:17.481 --> 55:18.651
Uh, it feels...

55:18.732 --> 55:23.072
Yeah, the whole thing just
feels so stiff and formal.

55:23.153 --> 55:26.163
I mean, it's not quite right yet, but
it will get there.

55:26.240 --> 55:29.870
Uh, Gavin, there's a Jack
Roth asking for you.

55:31.245 --> 55:34.285
I'm sorry, I need
to take this. Um...

55:34.373 --> 55:36.753
Yup, just tell him I'll
call him back on my cell.

55:37.209 --> 55:38.749
Sorry. Sorry.

55:38.961 --> 55:41.091
I guess we're taking a five.

55:43.340 --> 55:45.260
Hey, Jack, what in the world?

55:45.342 --> 55:46.982
This is important.
Why didn't you pick up?

55:47.094 --> 55:48.114
I'm in the middle of a scene.

55:48.136 --> 55:49.739
What are you talking about?
From the production.

55:49.763 --> 55:52.813
The church production
that I'm doing.

55:52.891 --> 55:53.952
I didn't tell you about this?

55:53.976 --> 55:55.411
No, I thought you were
doing maintenance.

55:55.435 --> 55:56.475
<i>I was.</i>

55:56.562 --> 55:59.192
But they cast me as Jesus in
their big Easter production.

55:59.273 --> 56:02.113
So now I get to act to work off my hours.
It worked out perfect.

56:02.192 --> 56:03.192
They cast you as who?

56:03.610 --> 56:04.610
Jesus.

56:07.322 --> 56:09.832
Yeah, look, what do
you want, Jack?

56:09.908 --> 56:12.738
Okay, this is
why I love you, kid.

56:12.828 --> 56:14.958
<i>Because I love you,
I took a chance with Meara.</i>

56:15.038 --> 56:16.078
So you got through to him?

56:16.123 --> 56:17.683
I remembered how much
he loved to party,

56:17.749 --> 56:19.229
so I told him
your little hotel story,

56:19.293 --> 56:20.653
but I spiced up your
role in the incident.

56:20.669 --> 56:22.399
<i>And said that you'd love
to catch up with him.</i>

56:22.421 --> 56:23.511
Yeah? And?

56:23.589 --> 56:25.669
And after he demanded
to see the pictures,

56:25.757 --> 56:28.757
he said that he'd keep an eye out
and that he would be in touch.

56:28.844 --> 56:30.224
That's great.

56:30.304 --> 56:32.594
If he gets in contact with you,
you better be all over it.

56:32.639 --> 56:34.929
You got that? I will,
I will, I promise.

56:35.017 --> 56:37.517
Okay, so, seriously, now
that you're a Christian,

56:37.603 --> 56:39.023
can you pray for me?

56:40.397 --> 56:41.727
Bye, Jack.

56:49.031 --> 56:52.451
My sister,
where are your accusers?

56:53.660 --> 56:55.040
Where are your accusers?

56:55.120 --> 56:56.160
Still not working for you?

56:57.789 --> 56:58.829
Hey.

56:59.291 --> 57:01.751
Thought you went home. No, I
was printing up the posters.

57:05.839 --> 57:07.719
Oh. Not bad.
"Not bad"?

57:07.799 --> 57:10.089
You, of all
people, should love it.

57:10.177 --> 57:12.257
I put you front and center.

57:12.804 --> 57:15.474
Gavin comes first.
What?

57:15.557 --> 57:17.847
Uh, that's Jack, my manager.

57:18.727 --> 57:22.267
"Kid, this is all you need
to know about show business.

57:22.689 --> 57:24.779
"Gavin comes first.

57:24.983 --> 57:27.533
"Everybody else, they just need
something from you.

57:27.611 --> 57:31.411
"You want to survive in this
business, you look out for you."

57:33.158 --> 57:34.448
Interesting advice.

57:34.534 --> 57:37.044
Yeah. I was eight.

57:38.038 --> 57:39.038
Wow.

57:39.122 --> 57:40.582
But it stuck.

57:40.999 --> 57:42.329
"Gavin comes first."

57:43.543 --> 57:46.673
Maybe that's why you have such a
hard time playing somebody humble.

57:47.422 --> 57:49.632
Yeah, maybe it is.

57:50.217 --> 57:51.467
Thank you, Dr. Phil.

57:52.260 --> 57:54.390
Wait, I have an idea.
What are you doing tomorrow?

57:54.471 --> 57:57.221
It's Saturday, so sleeping.

57:57.975 --> 58:01.135
Maybe I'll wake up early for lunch.
Not tomorrow.

58:01.228 --> 58:03.938
Meet Doug at the garage
by the parking lot at 9:00.

58:04.022 --> 58:05.362
A.M.?

58:05.524 --> 58:06.734
I did say it was Saturday.

58:06.817 --> 58:08.987
You said your character
wasn't coming easy, right?

58:09.069 --> 58:10.069
Maybe.

58:10.153 --> 58:12.243
Just show up. Trust me.

58:17.619 --> 58:19.159
Hello.
Hey, man.

58:19.246 --> 58:20.246
Hey.

58:20.288 --> 58:22.498
Kelly said you'd be coming by.
Yeah.

58:22.582 --> 58:24.132
Welcome to CFSM.

58:24.209 --> 58:26.089
Cars for single moms.

58:26.169 --> 58:28.879
Okay, so, what's happening?

58:29.256 --> 58:31.006
Well, first of all,
you're changing.

58:31.425 --> 58:34.755
I think I might actually
have something new for you.

58:35.178 --> 58:37.178
Here you go.
Put that on.

58:37.889 --> 58:40.639
Rusted catalytic converter,
detached from the exhaust system.

58:40.726 --> 58:43.346
The VCT solenoid valve
needs replacing,

58:43.437 --> 58:46.857
and there's a significant binding
in the brake pedal linkage.

58:47.399 --> 58:49.189
I have no idea
what those words mean.

58:49.276 --> 58:50.606
All right, first things first,

58:50.694 --> 58:53.664
you're gonna change the oil filter
while I work on the convertor.

58:53.739 --> 58:56.029
You've done that before, right?

59:09.212 --> 59:11.972
All right. Tightened all the way?
Yup.

59:12.049 --> 59:13.179
Okay.

59:14.509 --> 59:15.639
Done?

59:16.219 --> 59:17.219
Not quite.

59:28.523 --> 59:30.573
So, what do you think?

59:31.234 --> 59:32.884
Think I've got a truck
I can bring in next week.

59:32.903 --> 59:35.493
Watch this.
This is the best part.

59:48.418 --> 59:50.168
They always try
to pay something.

59:50.253 --> 59:53.173
No, no, this is on us.

59:54.841 --> 59:56.891
Why don't you go over there? No.

59:57.010 --> 59:59.890
Then she'd know who did it.
Yeah, exactly.

01:00:00.388 --> 01:00:02.428
We don't want the credit.

01:00:03.433 --> 01:00:05.983
Hashtag, words I've never
said to my agent.

01:00:06.812 --> 01:00:08.062
Exactly.

01:00:13.568 --> 01:00:14.858
Hey.
Hi.

01:00:15.862 --> 01:00:17.452
So, who was she?

01:00:17.739 --> 01:00:19.319
That was Olivia.

01:00:19.407 --> 01:00:22.787
Uh, two kids. She almost lost her job
'cause she couldn't get to it.

01:00:22.869 --> 01:00:23.999
But thanks to you...

01:00:24.246 --> 01:00:25.786
Oh! Come on,
thanks to Doug.

01:00:25.872 --> 01:00:29.382
You got a little smudge or
something on your outfit here.

01:00:29.584 --> 01:00:30.754
That's very funny.

01:00:31.545 --> 01:00:32.705
Thanks.

01:00:34.047 --> 01:00:35.297
I know I look ridiculous.

01:00:36.508 --> 01:00:38.388
It's not so bad.
This?

01:00:39.344 --> 01:00:41.184
It works on you.
Really?

01:00:41.263 --> 01:00:42.433
Yup.

01:00:47.227 --> 01:00:49.147
- You know what this means, don't you?
- Do tell.

01:00:49.187 --> 01:00:51.307
You're a free man.
What?

01:00:51.398 --> 01:00:52.918
I still have a couple
more hours, don't I?

01:00:52.941 --> 01:00:55.361
No. After your car work,
Saturday, you're over 200.

01:00:55.569 --> 01:00:58.609
Oh, no, that doesn't count. I don't
even want the hours for that.

01:00:58.697 --> 01:01:00.027
Really? Thank you.

01:01:00.323 --> 01:01:02.163
Well, then, after
rehearsal, you'll be done.

01:01:02.242 --> 01:01:03.742
I'll turn this in today, anyway.

01:01:03.952 --> 01:01:06.502
I gotta tell you, Gavin, you have
really livened this place up.

01:01:06.580 --> 01:01:08.020
You've been a great
addition to our church.

01:01:08.039 --> 01:01:10.184
And you've made my daughter's
life a little easier, too.

01:01:10.208 --> 01:01:12.288
Thank you. Thank you
for the second chance.

01:01:12.752 --> 01:01:15.402
All right, now I'm gonna need you to
pray for a full house this weekend.

01:01:15.422 --> 01:01:16.512
Way ahead of you.

01:01:20.010 --> 01:01:22.180
So how's the Messiah doing?

01:01:22.345 --> 01:01:24.965
Hey, guys. We're not on for
another 10 minutes, right?

01:01:25.056 --> 01:01:26.736
I know, but we wanted...
We just decided...

01:01:26.808 --> 01:01:28.244
We just thought...
Well, we got you something.

01:01:28.268 --> 01:01:30.058
Years ago, when we
dedicated this building,

01:01:30.145 --> 01:01:31.685
pastor Allan did
something really cool.

01:01:31.771 --> 01:01:33.691
Gave each church member
a nail from the building.

01:01:33.773 --> 01:01:34.773
We all kept ours.

01:01:34.858 --> 01:01:38.278
We just thought since you're
a part of the family now,

01:01:38.612 --> 01:01:40.532
that you should have them.

01:01:40.614 --> 01:01:41.664
Ah...

01:01:49.080 --> 01:01:50.330
Do you like it?

01:01:50.582 --> 01:01:52.672
Thank you, guys.

01:01:54.961 --> 01:01:56.961
I don't know what to say.

01:01:58.840 --> 01:02:01.340
All right, it's last
week of rehearsals.

01:02:01.801 --> 01:02:03.431
Let's crush this.

01:02:04.304 --> 01:02:05.644
All right.
Gavin?

01:02:06.264 --> 01:02:07.274
Oh, yeah.

01:02:13.855 --> 01:02:15.015
Okay, exit Jesus.

01:02:15.398 --> 01:02:17.818
Houselights, please.
Houselights.

01:02:19.110 --> 01:02:21.110
You guys, that was great.

01:02:23.531 --> 01:02:24.781
Whoo!

01:02:25.200 --> 01:02:27.330
It's really coming
together, you guys.

01:02:27.410 --> 01:02:30.120
We will pick up work tomorrow morning.
We'll go over tweaks then.

01:02:30.205 --> 01:02:31.995
Just call it a night, okay?

01:02:32.415 --> 01:02:34.415
Hey, um, I have
a few notes for you,

01:02:34.501 --> 01:02:36.651
but l have some last minute costume
alterations I need to do.

01:02:36.670 --> 01:02:38.650
I was thinking maybe you could
meet me at my place in a bit.

01:02:38.672 --> 01:02:40.592
I'll make you coffee.
You asking me on a date?

01:02:40.674 --> 01:02:42.844
Whatever you need.
Just get there, okay?

01:02:43.843 --> 01:02:49.773
All right, all right. Just like to
be courted a little bit. That's all.

01:02:57.732 --> 01:02:59.402
<i>Hello.
Gavin stone?</i>

01:02:59.943 --> 01:03:01.823
Long time, no talk.

01:03:01.903 --> 01:03:03.363
Yeah, it has been.

01:03:03.446 --> 01:03:05.816
<i>So, I got some good news.
Like the sound of that.</i>

01:03:05.907 --> 01:03:07.407
Long story, short.

01:03:07.492 --> 01:03:09.052
Your man, Jack,
told me about that rager

01:03:09.077 --> 01:03:11.287
<i>you threw on the roof
not too long ago.</i>

01:03:11.371 --> 01:03:15.041
Yeah. Yeah, man,
it was something.

01:03:15.375 --> 01:03:16.955
<i>Ah! What an animal!</i>

01:03:17.043 --> 01:03:18.923
I got so inspired by the story,

01:03:19.004 --> 01:03:21.304
that I scrapped
a character in my show,

01:03:21.381 --> 01:03:22.531
<i>and I rewrote one just for you.</i>

01:03:22.549 --> 01:03:23.549
What?
Yeah.

01:03:23.633 --> 01:03:25.593
<i>And I want you to come
out to la to play it.</i>

01:03:25.677 --> 01:03:28.347
A series regular.
I need that bad boy energy.

01:03:29.431 --> 01:03:31.221
<i>Uh...
I got network approval.</i>

01:03:31.308 --> 01:03:33.098
And the PR,
they love the whole thing

01:03:33.184 --> 01:03:34.894
about the child actor
playing the druggie.

01:03:34.978 --> 01:03:37.898
<i>We shoot as soon as
you hit the set tomorrow.</i>

01:03:41.192 --> 01:03:43.612
<i>It shoots tomorrow?
It is the real deal.</i>

01:03:43.695 --> 01:03:46.025
<i>I'm in Chicago, man.
This is the big leagues, bro.</i>

01:03:46.114 --> 01:03:48.834
You got a first class ticket waiting
for you right now at O'Hare.

01:03:48.908 --> 01:03:53.078
Well, you know this production I'm
doing, it runs through the weekend.

01:03:53.163 --> 01:03:55.003
Yeah, Jack mentioned
something about that.

01:03:55.081 --> 01:03:58.461
Yeah, it's a stage production
of the Bible, actually.

01:03:58.585 --> 01:04:00.085
TMZ's gonna eat that one up.

01:04:00.378 --> 01:04:03.468
<i>Well, whatever it is,
you got a back-up, right?</i>

01:04:03.631 --> 01:04:04.761
Yeah.

01:04:05.216 --> 01:04:07.046
Yeah, there's a guy, Charles.

01:04:07.135 --> 01:04:08.505
<i>Great, so you got it covered.</i>

01:04:08.595 --> 01:04:10.505
This is not gonna
happen twice, all right?

01:04:10.597 --> 01:04:13.177
<i>Not for you. So like I
said, I need to know.</i>

01:04:13.266 --> 01:04:14.516
<i>Are you in?</i>

01:04:14.601 --> 01:04:16.101
<i>Are you stupid?</i>

01:04:17.312 --> 01:04:18.942
I'll see you in la tomorrow.

01:05:06.569 --> 01:05:09.449
Charlotte just called me.
Okay.

01:05:09.531 --> 01:05:11.871
She said she overheard you
on the phone with some la guy.

01:05:11.950 --> 01:05:15.250
She heard you agree to leave
tonight for some shoot.

01:05:15.328 --> 01:05:16.968
I told her that
she must have heard wrong.

01:05:17.038 --> 01:05:20.538
That there's no way you're leaving
three days before opening night.

01:05:20.625 --> 01:05:23.125
That nobody,
not even Gavin stone,

01:05:23.211 --> 01:05:25.001
would do something that selfish.

01:05:25.171 --> 01:05:26.671
Please tell me she's wrong.

01:05:28.341 --> 01:05:31.681
It shoots for three weeks
in la starting tomorrow.

01:05:31.886 --> 01:05:33.676
There's a plane waiting
for me right now.

01:05:34.472 --> 01:05:35.682
I'm gonna be on it.

01:05:38.393 --> 01:05:39.393
This isn't happening.

01:05:39.477 --> 01:05:40.847
Look, I'm sorry.

01:05:40.979 --> 01:05:42.359
You're sorry?

01:05:42.981 --> 01:05:44.671
Say it again, I'm sure
it'll make me feel better.

01:05:44.691 --> 01:05:45.691
Kelly...

01:05:45.775 --> 01:05:48.695
Do you know that I have a
voicemail message from my dad

01:05:48.778 --> 01:05:52.988
saying that every seat in the house
is reserved for opening night.

01:05:53.074 --> 01:05:55.294
Charles will be happy
to step in.

01:05:55.368 --> 01:05:57.078
Everything we changed
still works.

01:05:57.162 --> 01:06:01.122
Your name and face are on the poster!
Are you out of your mind?

01:06:01.207 --> 01:06:03.077
I can't say no to this.

01:06:03.710 --> 01:06:05.840
Hollywood isn't like church.

01:06:05.920 --> 01:06:07.800
Second chances
don't just come around.

01:06:07.881 --> 01:06:09.591
What am I supposed
to tell the cast?

01:06:12.385 --> 01:06:15.715
I think that god has
something bigger for me.

01:06:15.805 --> 01:06:18.845
God has nothing to do with this.

01:06:18.933 --> 01:06:22.103
How do you know? Doesn't god
want me to pursue my dream?

01:06:22.187 --> 01:06:23.477
To be happy?

01:06:23.563 --> 01:06:25.483
I can't believe this.

